    "body": "### Description\n\nI was trying to set up an `BufWritePre` action for the `tailwindcss` server like this:\n\n```lua\n      lspconfig.tailwindcss.setup({\n        capabilities = cmp_lsp.default_capabilities(),\n        on_attach = function(client, bufnr)\n          vim.notify(\"HI FROM TAILWIND\")\n          vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"BufWritePre\", {\n            buffer = bufnr,\n            callback = function()\n              vim.cmd(\"TailwindSortSync\")\n            end,\n          })\n        end,\n      })\n```\n\nHowever, I never see `HI FROM TAILWIND` and the autocmd never registers. I modified `nvim-lspconfig` source locally to add some logging:\n\n```diff\n@@ -280,6 +280,12 @@ function configs.__newindex(t, config_name, config_def)\n       return\n     end\n     local config = client.config --[[@as lspconfig.Config]]\n+    vim.notify(\n+      'Working on '\n+        .. client.name\n+        .. ' with config '\n+        .. vim.inspect({ on_attach = config.on_attach, _attach_two = config._on_attach })\n+    )\n     if config._on_attach then\n       config._on_attach(client, bufnr)\n     end\n```\n\nWhen I pass `on_attach` to my setup of other language servers (I've tried `typescript-tools` and `biome`), then the log line contains both `on_attach` as well as `_on_attach`. However, when I pass it to `tailwindcss`, I only ever see `on_attach`,  and never `_on_attach`. This makes me suspect that the bug may be within Neovim source code somewhere. But it seems worthwhile posting it here.\n\nThe output is:\n\n```\nWorking on biome with config {\n  _on_attach = <function 1>,\n  on_attach = <function 2>\n}\nHI FROM BIOME\nWorking on tailwindcss with config {\n  on_attach = <function 1>\n}\nWorking on typescript-tools with config {\n  _on_attach = <function 1>,\n  on_attach = <function 2>\n}\nHI FROM TSSERVER\nPress ENTER or type command to continue\n```\n\nHere are the contents of my `lsp.log` after opening a file that attaches the `tailwindcss` server:\n\n```\n[START][2024-11-03 11:40:29] LSP logging initiated\n[WARN][2024-11-03 11:40:29] ...lsp/handlers.lua:625\t\"Language mappings are currently set via initialization options (`userLanguages`). This is deprecated and will be removed in a future release. Please use the `tailwindCSS.includeLanguages` setting instead.\"\n[WARN][2024-11-03 11:40:30] ...lsp/handlers.lua:135\t\"The language server tailwindcss triggers a registerCapability handler for workspace/didChangeWorkspaceFolders despite dynamicRegistration set to false. Report upstream, this warning is harmless\"\n```",
